a\cos (x) + b\sin (x) = \sqrt{a^2+b^2}\cos (x - p),\text{ where }\tan(p)=\frac ba.
\sqrt2\cos(1)-\sqrt2\sin(1)=-0.43=2\cos(1-p_1),\text{ where }\tan(p_1)=-1,
-\sqrt2\cos(1)+\sqrt2\sin(1)=0.43=2\cos(1-p_2),\text{ where }\tan(p_2)=-1.
